I looked through this backport. I don't see any amphora agent API changes, Octavia API changes, or database migrations. I think this fix is acceptable as a stable branch backport. It is sizable, which brings some risk, but moving away from the distro network management tools is important to solve some stability issues we have had with them.
LGTM

Hello, do you think is it possible to ask for someone to merge these changes to avoid possible future conflicts and rebases.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

Hi Hervé

The charmhelpers module that we sync into the charms in manages here https://github.com/juju/charm-helpers.  Any changes made directly in the charm will be lost when we next re-sync.

This codebase is still py2 and py3 compatibility as there are a number of charms in the wide ecosystem that still use Python 2.

Patch Set 2:

Note, the test_charm_func_full error is because "Func-Test-PR" in the commit message needs to be committed first.
AttributeError: module 'zaza.openstack.charm_tests.cinder.tests' has no attribute 'TLSSecurityTests'

Patch Set 2:

The point of the func-test-pr line is that it allows us to test the functional gate before landing the changes in the PR. I suspect that the actual issue is that the trailing slash is messing with the automatic replacement of the package in the test-requirements.txt and so it isn't being pulled in.

Patch Set 2:

For reference, https://bazaar.launchpad.net/~uosci/ubuntu-openstack-ci/trunk/view/head:/run/job-parts/osci_openstack_common.sh#L186 is the specific match that is used to find a func-test-pr

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

A bit of teseting confirms it, when there is a trailing '/', the PR parsing function parses the PR into 'zaza-openstack-tests/pull/'; whereas, without the trailing '/', it parses 'openstack-charmers/zaza-openstack-tests/343'.

$ echo "Func-Test-PR: https://github.com/openstack-charmers/zaza-openstack-tests/pull/343/" | awk 'tolower($0) ~ /func-test-pr: .*github.*zaza.*pull/ {print $2; exit;}' | rev | cut -sf1,3,4 -d/ | rev
zaza-openstack-tests/pull/
$ echo "Func-Test-PR: https://github.com/openstack-charmers/zaza-openstack-tests/pull/343" | awk 'tolower($0) ~ /func-test-pr: .*github.*zaza.*pull/ {print $2; exit;}' | rev | cut -sf1,3,4 -d/ | rev
openstack-charmers/zaza-openstack-tests/343

Patch Set 5: Workflow-1

Fixed an issue (and added a respective test) in the card_serial_number property.

Also, this patch will need to be reworked to match an upcoming v6 revision of the Libvirt patch: for Nova it will mean that different XML element names will be used, hence WF-1 for now.

Patch Set 5:

Whether the VPD capability is exposed on VFs or not turns out to be NIC firmware specific. For example, Bluefield devices have a firmware setting that allows enabling VPD exposure on VFs.

$ sudo mlxconfig -d /dev/mst/mt41686_pciconf0 q | grep -i vpd
         VF_VPD_ENABLE                       False(0)    

However, this is not universal across NICs and it is probably worth extending this patch to also attempt to pull VPD information from a parent PF if it is not available on a VF - that would make it more universal across different hardware and firmware implementations.
